  CoLinux Lite  ·  Alpine Linux + OpenAI Codex CLI
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  System:  Alpine $(cat /etc/alpine-release 2>/dev/null || echo unknown)
  Kernel:  $(uname -r 2>/dev/null || echo unknown)
  Arch:    $(uname -m 2>/dev/null || echo unknown)
  Codex:   $(codex --version 2>/dev/null || echo "not installed")

  Workspace: /workspace
  Config:    /persist/config/
  Logs:      /persist/logs/

  Type 'codex' to start, or 'codexctl' for system commands.

  ── Rules ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  • Always run codex-disk-inventory before accessing foreign disks
  • Mount unknown filesystems read-only first
  • Log important actions to /persist/logs/
  • See /workspace/AGENTS.md for full operating guidelines

